{Find the most promising plan for Black in this position.} 17... Rab8 $1 {
Getting ready for c6-c5.} 18. Na4 $2 {This is simply bad, as it doesn't
prevent Black's idea.} (18. Qc2 {was safer, but after} c5 19. dxc5 Nxc5 $15 {
, Black has a comfortable position.}) 18... c5 $1 19. dxc5 $2 ({It was not too
late for} 19. Nc3 cxd4 20. Nxd4 Nc5 $15 {, when White is only slightly worse.})
19... Nxc5 20. Rxd8+ Qxd8 21. Nxc5 bxc5 {White's position seems already
desperate now.} 22. Qc2 {Obolenskikh,D (2510)-Sjugirov,S (2622)/Moscow op-A
2012 (3)/0-1 The simplest path for Black now was} Bxf3 23. Bxf3 Bxb2 24. Rd1
Qc7 25. a4 Be5 $19 {[%csl Rc5][%cal Rb8b2] , with a winning advantage.} *

