16. axb4 Nf6 $11 {, Black can keep pressure on both d4 and b4, with a good
game.}) 15... Qxa5 16. Qb3 O-O 17. Rfc1 (17. Nxb5 $2 {looks like a clever
tactic, but it is actually a blunder:} Qb6 $1 $19 {, and Black wins.}) 17...
Rfb8 $15 {[%cal Gc6c5] ;Banikas,H (2576)-Van Wely,L (2655)/Olympiad-37 Turin
2006 (4)/0-1, and Black had a pleasant position.}) ({White can also try the
interesting move order} 7. e3 g6 8. e4 $5 {, which leads to interesting
positions due to the new weaknesses in Black's camp. For purposes of better
