and Black launched a dangerous attack.}) 10. Qd3 (10. Qc2 {was played in a
recent game:} f5 $1 11. Nc3 (11. Ned2 {looks safer, but Black still has} c5 12.
a3 Bxd2 13. Qxd2 Qc7 {, with a nice position.}) 11... c5 $1 {this is the point:
