16... Rc7 $146 17. Qd1 Rac8 {is an alternative to keep the tension, with a
balanced position.}) (16... e5 $5 $146 {looks more principled. I initially
thought that it was an error due to} 17. dxe5 Nxe5 18. Nxe5 Qxe5 19. Nb6 $2 {
[%csl Ga8,Gc8] , but it turns out that White is the side in trouble after} c3
$1 20. Nxa8 cxb2 21. Qxc8+ Bxc8 22. Rxc8+ Kh7 23. Bd3+ g6 24. Rf1 a4 $17 {
[%csl Ga4,Gb2] The queenside pawns are too powerful and will soon force White
