precise?} 11... a6 $1 ({It is important to remember that after} 11... Qd6 {
, White simply continues with the plan,} 12. b5 $1 {, as the Nc3 is defended
by the rook, depriving Black of the typical reaction c6-c5 - which is the
reason for bringing the queen to d6. After} O-O 13. O-O Nb6 14. bxc6 bxc6 15.
Na4 $14 {[%csl Ga7,Gc6] , White has achieved the typical superior structure of
