compensation for the pawn:} 12. Ne5 Nxe5 (12... O-O 13. Ne4 $5) 13. dxe5 Nd7
14. Ne4 $1 {The idea of sacrificing a second pawn is fully sound.} Nxe5 ({
In case of} 14... O-O {, White has the strong idea} 15. a5 $1 Bxa5 16. f4 $1
Bb4 17. Rf3 $18 {[%cal Rf3g3] , and Black suddenly faces a crushing attack.})
15. a5 $1 Qc7 {Nepomniachtchi,I (2784) -Kramnik,V (2753)/Legends of Chess
Prelim rapid 2020 (1.2)/0-1 In this position, Nepo missed the strong
continuation} 16. a6 Bc8 17. b3 $5 {which seemed very promising for White, for
