Qxb3 Be7 19. Bxe7 Qxe7 20. Qc3 f6 21. Bh5+ $36 {, when White's initiative
looks very dangerous.}) 12. Bxf6 $5 {I think in practice, this is the only way
to exploit White's small lead in development.} (12. e4 {is too slow and gives
Black time to mobilize his forces.} a6 13. Rfd1 Bb7 14. Ne5 (14. e5 Nd5 15. Ne4
c5 $19) 14... Qc7 15. Nxd7 (15. Bg3 {is also harmless.} Nxe5 16. Bxe5 Qe7 $17 {
[%cal Yf6d7]}) 15... Nxd7 16. Bg4 {Nikologorskiy,K (2398)-Aleksandrov,A (2637)/
Izhevsk Corporation Cup 5th 2013 (7)/0-1} Nb6 $17 {It is easy to see that
