{White has sacrificed a second pawn to cramp Black's position. How would you
try to create counterplay?} 22... Qg5 $1 ({On the other hand, after the hasty} 
22... g3 $4 23. f4 $18 {, Black is completely dominated.}) 23. g3 Bxg3 24. fxg3
{Black hopes to get attacking chances on the kingside.} Rc8 25. Bxa5 (25. Bd6
Qe3+ 26. Kh2 c5 $1 {[%csl Gb7][%cal Yg8g5,Yg5h5] looks very tense.}) 25... Qe3+
26. Kh2 Rg5 $1 {[%cal Gg5h5]} 27. Nc5 $1 {Avoiding c6-c5, which would be
winning for Black. The likely result is a draw, after correct play by both
sides:} Rh5+ 28. Kg2 Rh3 29. Qd3 Rxg3+ 30. Kh2 Rh3+ 31. Kg2 Rg3+ $11 *

