{What's the best reaction to White's principled advance d4-d5?} 11... cxd5 $1 {
Not afraid of ghosts!} ({The opening of the e-file leads to sad consequences
for Black:} 11... exd5 $2 12. exd5 Nxd5 13. Bxc4 $1 $18 {[%csl Re8][%cal Rf1e1]
}) 12. exd5 (12. Nxb5 $2 {might look good, but after} Nxe4 $1 13. Nc7+ Ke7 14.
Nxa8 Qxa8 $19 {Kosov,V (2108)-Kozirev,A (2367)/Cheliabinsk City-ch 2008 (8)/
0-1, Black has two pawns and a beautiful centre for the exchange.}) 12... Nxd5
13. Nxb5 a6 $1 14. Nd6+ Bxd6 15. Bxd6 {The bishop looks very strong on d6, but
Black is able to disturb it with} N7b6 16. Bc5 Qc7 17. Bxb6 (17. Ba3 $2 O-O-O
$1 $19) 17... Nxb6 18. Qd4 {And now} Ke7 $1 {Radjabov,T (2761)-Anand,V (2791)/
Linares 26th 2009 (8)/1/2-1/2 was a nice way to solve Black's opening problems.
} *

